text: Okay. This film isn’t probably gonna be good. Lemme explain why, The trailer portrays a person in a high political status with an agenda for the plot in this film. The classic good guys vs bad guys in movies. People aren’t really excited for this same old Shtick (don’t know how to spell it correctly). A good idea for the purge saga is to make a movie about a person who is purging over the loss of a loved one or just the person looking for revenge in the night of the purge. text: Ever since the purge took a political turn its been shit. First one was fucking great, and although the film location was only within one household, it was a believable movie and made me crave to see more of what the purge world looks like. The second film lived up to that, literally showing civilians purging in downtown L.A. which i fucking loved! Then came the third purge which felt so fucking... i dont even know, although it had a plot that made sense it felt so rushed and over the top with so much different things happening and unnecessary scenes that it made no sense. This movie seems like such a budget film, honestly youd think theyd have a way better ran down for a film showing the first ever purge. I was hoping to see a lot more chaos and pandemonium... innocent crowds of people seeing it as an excuse to loot mixed with and being brutally killed off by the people realising first hand that they are literally getting away with murder and realising and releasing the phyco we've all built up inside of us throughout our lives. Not this fucking 'lets group up and solve a mystery of whats really going on here cause something sure seems fishy' theme

text: As much as I like the Purge movies, they couldn't work in reality. If all crime is only legal for twelve hours per year, then most of people's preparation for crimes would also need to be done in those twelve hours. There are loads of other logistical things that wouldn't work, such as there would be no way to tell if some crimes had been committed just before or just after the purge time zone. The cleaning up of the mess and the long, drawn-out court cases would take more than a year. As it is, comparatively minor crimes can take years to go through the courts.
